Spectre Circuit Simulator Components and Device Models Reference
Product Version 23.1, June 2023

Component tatements

This device is supported within altergroups.

Name  d  g  s  e  [t] ModelName parameter=value ...

Model Syntax

model modelName bsimcmg parameter=value ...

Model Parameters

version

105.03

The model parameter "version" only accepts a real number value, like 106.1 for version=106.1.0. The available versions are 105.03, 105.031, 105.04, 106.0(106.0.0), 106.1(106.1.0), 107.0(107.0.0), 108.0(108.0.0), 110.0(110.0.0), 111.0(111.0.0), 111.1(111.1.0), 111.2(111.2.0) and 111.21(111.2.1).

coremod

0

0: Default surface potential algorithm, 1: Simplified (efficient) surface potential algorithm.

geomod

1

Structure selector. 0: Double gate, 1: Triple gate, 2: Quadruple gate, 3: Cylindrical gate, 4: Unified Fin Shape ( since version 110.0.0 ).

mobmod

0

0: BSIM4-based mobility model, 1: PSP-based mobility model.

rdsmod

0

Internal s/d resistance model, 1: External s/d resistance model , 2: Both bias dependent and independent part of source/drain resistance internal.

asymmod

0

0: Asymmetry Model turned off - forward mode parameters used, 1: Asymmetry Model turned on.

igcmod

0

0: Turn off Igc, Igs and Igd, 1: Turn on Igc, Igs and Igd.

igbmod

0

0: Turn off Igb, 1: Turn on Igb.

gidlmod

0

0: Turn off GIDL/GISL current, 1: Turn on GIDL/GISL current, 2: Turn on GIDL/GISL with parasitic substrate component for GEOMOD = 2 or 3 or 5 and BULKMOD != 0.

iimod

0

0: No impact ionization current, 1: BSIM4-based model, 2: BSIMSOI-based model, 3: TSMC specific model.

nqsmod

0

0: NQS models turned off, 1: NQS gate resistance / gi node turned on, 2: NQS charge deficit model (BSIM4) / q node turned on, 3: //NQS charge segmentation model / Nseg nodes turned on.

shmod

0

0: No self-heating, 1: Self-heating turned on.

rgatemod

0

0: Gate electrode resistance / ge node turned off, 1: Gate electrode resistance / ge node turned on.

rgeomod

0

Geometry-dependent source/drain resistance. 0: RSH-based, 1: Holistic.

cgeomod

0

Geometry-dependent parasitic capacitance,model selector.

capmod

0

0: No accumulation capacitance, 1: Accumulation capacitance included. Available only for BULKMOD = 1.

0

The number indicates where to look in the appropriate section to find the description for that parameter. For example, a reference of M-35 means the 35th model parameter.
